{"id": "1489130451053318276", "channel_id": "1489130451053318276", "type": 0, "author_id": "536798865588748308", "author_name": "xdontacox", "author_bot": false, "content": "I know this idea is not for everyone, personally , I started playing this game because of slay the spire, monster train etc. and I love that difficulty.\n\nIn these games you are not supposed to win every run, and you are supposed to continuously struggle, and funnily enough, Morimens already has everything you need, and MORE CONTENT than every single one of these games, I have been playing underleveled and at the beginning it was great, it was that exact experience, I got fights where both me and the boss did a finishing blow in the same turn and I live because of the avoid death mechanic, I don't think devs realize that their game, being a gacha game, can deliver more than slay the spire.\n\nThen I pulled Wanda, and I destroy everything even underleveled, AND on top of the vame being easy now, I am still underleveled, meaning I have gated myself from endgame content, events, and the rewards that comes with this content.\n\nAnd this is easily applicable, if devs added the option to handicap your team, in that very exact moment they created a game that beats every rouge like card battled, because this game has more playable characters than every single one, more bosses, more stages. \n\nThe game I am playing is better than slay the spire, I swear to god I am being honest, but I am not playing like devs intended me to, and I can not recommend doing what I do to anyone, because that means getting less rewards.\n\nTLDR: devs, trust me, just let us handicap our characters, skills etc, it would make EVERY SINGLE STAGE infinitely replayable", "timestamp": "2026-04-02T05:12:46.237000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "👆", "emoji_id": null, "count": 5}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1489130451053318276", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Allow us to lower the level of our characters during investigations... please let me explain", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
